quran[19]{c,v,t}:
  21,94,"Whoever shall do good deeds, provided he is a believer, his endeavor will not be rejected: We are recording it all for him"
  21,95,It is not possible that a nation which We have destroyed may rise again
  21,96,"Until, when Gog and Magog will be let loose and they will swiftly swarm from every height"
  21,97,"and the time of fulfillment for the True Promise will draw near, then behold! The eyes of the unbelievers will fixedly stare in horror: \"O woe to us! We were indeed heedless of this warning; nay we were wrongdoers"
  21,98,Surely you (O pagans) and your deities that you worship besides Allah shall be the fuel of hell; therein you shall all enter
  21,99,"If those deities would have been true gods, they would not have gotten there; but there they shall abide forever"
  21,100,"In there, sobbing will be their lot, and they will not be able to hear anything else"
  21,101,Certainly those for whom the good reward from Us has preceded them will be kept far away from it
  21,102,"They shall not hear even its slightest sound, and they shall dwell forever in the midst of whatever their souls desire"
  21,103,"The time of Great Terror (Day of Judgement) will not grieve them, and the angels will receive them with greetings: \"This is your Day that you were promised"
  21,104,"On that Day We shall roll up the heavens like a scroll of writings; just as We originated the first creation, so shall We produce it again - that is Our promise, and We will fulfill it"
  21,105,"We wrote this in The Zaboor (Psalms xxxvii, 29) after the reminder (Torah given to Moses): that as for the land, My righteous servants shall inherit it"
  21,106,Surely in this is great news for those people who worship Us
  21,107,"O Muhammad, We have not sent you but as a blessing for all the worlds"
  21,108,"Tell them: \"It has been revealed to me that your God is One God - will you then become Muslims"
  21,109,"If they give no heed, tell them: \"I have warned you all alike in complete fairness; now I do not know whether what you are threatened with is near or far"
  21,110,It is He Who knows your spoken words and hidden thoughts
  21,111,I do not know whether this delay is a trial for you or you are being given respite for an appointed time
  21,112,"Finally the Prophet said: \"O Lord! Pass Your Judgment with fairness. And O People! Our Lord is most Compassionate, Whose help we seek against the blasphemies you utter"